metadata.name: Geometriland #5
metadata.description:
The Geometriland token is another in a series of tokens of a larger project called Kim Blood 2024. 

It now comes in a code-only version, without loading graphics or other libraries. 
Pure js code contains 676 lines, 20744 characters without spaces.

This is a generative rendering of nature using geometric shapes in a two-color design.
Using params you can set colors, serrations and round stamp. 
The rendering of nature depends on chance. 
There are endless variations.

Image resolution: 2150x1700px
You can download the PNG after pressing the "s" key.

metadata.name: YYYSEED #893
metadata.description:
🔥 BURN NOTICE: This is a FIVE DAY "open edition" to celebrate the launch of fx(params). The project is open for minting from the start of Monday until midnight Friday (GMT).

YYYSEED is an artwork with an aesthetic that works across digital, print and pen plotting mediums, leaning towards the minimalistic nature of drawing machines. SVGs can be exported for this purpose.

I've designed the algorithm to work best for this with the default settings, you should be good to go right out of the box. You can explore the design space a little further using the parameters (more details below).

If you're planning on plotting the work at larger sizes (A2, A1), then the "Override suggest lines" is there for you to cram more of them into the extra space.

PARAMS ::::::::::::::

The initial settings of the parameters are what I think best for the look I'm trying to achieve as the artist: minimal pen plotting work. This comes from the "Suggested" and "Random for hash" values.

You can take the design away from that by turning the "Use suggested lines" and "Use suggested destroyer" options off, and using your own values with the slider.

"Random for hash" means the feature has been randomly selected and fixed for the current hash and won't change. For example, if the hash is 'ooABCD' and the grid's "Random for hash" picks 3x4, then it will always be 3x4 for that hash, it isn't random each time you change sometime. Picking a new hash however will then randomly pick a new (fixed) option.

DANGER SEED :::::::::

USE OF THE DANGER SEED IS NOT RECOMMENDED. If you set the DANGER SEED, the value will be encoded along with the rest of the params (where it can be decoded) in the stored data of the mint, along with the token.

The DANGER SEED will only take effect if it starts with 'YYY', it will STOMP all over the other settings, including the hash.

INSTRUCTIONS ::::::::

h - Toggle highres mode on/off (starts off)
t - Toggle paper background on/off
s - Save png (in highres if toggled on)
1-6 - Save SVGs for plotting A1, A2, A3, A4, A5, A6

PEN PLOTTING ::::::::

Press 1-6 to select which A1-6 size paper you want to plot onto, the the system will download one or more files for you to use, one file per colour.

Please tag #plottertwitter, or #penplotter on twitter, instagram & mastodon

PRINTING ::::::::::::

The output of the high resolution version is 6,144 x 8,192 pixels. That will print at the following sizes.

300dpi: 20.48 x 27.31 inches (52.02 x 69.35 cm)
200dpi: 30.72 x 40.96 inches (78.03 x 104.03 cm)

300dpi is recommended, but 200dpi should be fine for this design. I suggest turning the paper texture off if you're printing onto textured archival paper, you can leave it on when printing onto smooth white paper.

metadata.name: Dialog Box #129
metadata.description:
Dialog Box is a playful generative art project that invites viewers to engage with the concept of choice in the digital age. Inspired by the early Mac OS, the artwork presents an interface of two buttons, each symbolizing a choice steeped in 80s and 90s pop culture, from the serious to the lighthearted.

https://medium.com/@duaneking/dialog-box-by-duane-king-scott-brewer-and-adam-moliski-abab7afd3519

metadata.name: Observance #2
metadata.description:
Happy birthday fxhash!

Observance is a collection of 365 pieces, one to mark each day of fxhash's first year.

4 seasons
7 days
12 months
365 dates

Each piece has an alternate birthday palette & all pieces can be saved as an SVG for plotting

Hit 'p' in live mode to save a 3720 × 5262px PNG
Hit 's' in live mode to save a plottable SVG

This is a generative NFT work by aotearoan, 2022

50% of proceeds go to support Processing.org

License: CC BY-NC-SA-4.0

metadata.name: Dancing in Meadow #12
metadata.description:
"She felt the breeze caress her skin as she twirled under the shade of the old oak tree. The birds sang along to the melody in her heart, and the sun smiled down on her with warmth and joy. She danced with grace and freedom, letting go of her worries and fears. She was one with the meadow, the wind, the birds, and the sun."
This generative graphics project consists of 33 layers that can generate 11760 different random pieces.

metadata.name: Arto #3
metadata.description: Arto is a pixel art character created by the mind. This artwork was designed in 25.25 px and then resized to 1024.1024 resolution. the number of traits in this project is 9 and 42 layers. it has the ability to make 691,200 differnt Arto.

metadata.name: Helix dancers #4
metadata.description: In the heart of the meadow, the sun stretched its golden arms, awakening the world with its warm embrace. Rays of sunlight danced like radiant whispers, painting the landscape in hues of amber and emerald. As the sun ascended, it ignited a symphony of life, coaxing flowers to unfurl and leaves to shimmer in its radiant glow. Nature's helixes, be they delicate tendrils or robust vines, reached upward like enthusiastic dancers, embracing the sun's energy with a graceful rhythm. In this harmonious ballet, the sun, its rays, and the uprising helixes united to weave a tale of vitality and renewal beneath the celestial stage.

metadata.name: Quintessence #126
metadata.description:
"Quintessence is a form of dark energy, more precisely a scalar field, postulated as an explanation of the observation of an accelerating rate of expansion of the universe. Dark and dynamic energy, the fifth and fundamental element of the universe." This artwork is inspired by this concept and tries to show a conflict between dark energy and matter that shapes the world around us. 

A heterogeneous and harmonious tension that sporadically creates a sense of transformation and conflict. Various Color Palettes and dimensions have been used.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the artwork.

Made with P5js.

metadata.name: caixes 🔊 #8
metadata.description:
CLICK TO START
-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated. 


Caixes (boxes):
-8 to 24 rows.
-24 to 48 active boxes in each row (the length of each row is at least the double).
-Full boxes contains one of 8 possible sounds.
-Rows move in two possible directions and have diferent velocities and sizes.
-when two adjacent boxes have the same sound type, are full and diferent directions, the synthesizer for that sound is activated.
-when they are activated, there is a possibility that the two lines that contain the sound boxes, change their position.

Params:

"Show empty boxes": show(true) empty boxes.
"Dark Mode": Dark (true) / light (false) mode.
"Squares/Rects": Squares (true): height of boxes have the same value of width / rects(false) height of boxes fill all the space.
"Squares/Rects": 0 to 1-> thikness of vertical lines.
"Flash intensity": when two rows are swaped, a flash is activated. Intensity of this flash (low, mid, high)
"Frequency Range": Frequency range of sounds. (random, all, low, high)
"Wave shapes": Select unique wave shape for all sounds (sine, sawtooth, square, triangle) or all of them randomly assigned to each sound.

Features:

"cols": number of active boxes (in screen) for each row (24-48)
"rows": number of rows (8-24)
"check_frames": the boxes are checked every check_frames(8-28)
"same_freq": same frequencies for all rows
"ratio_full": ratio of full boxes over total boxes.
"avg_boxes": average boxes/row
"avg_velocity": average velocity,
"fx_prob": probability of sound effects (less is more),
"change_prob": probability of row swap.


-powered by p5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: blind hole/ #8
metadata.description:
Synthesis modulated by protruding gems 💎

Gem count, size, and shape are randomly generated based on the minted hash. Any combination of 1 to 6 rows and columns of gems are available, some more rare than others. The colour palette has 5 options; rainbow, or red, green, or blue weighted, with the fifth option being a rare black and white.
